snippet.textDisplay:
I have a redmi k20 so the scope for customization is higher for me. Here is what I have done:
Used Nova launcher
Used pixel experience theme from the Xiaomi theme store ( this also changed my boot animation to be like pixel phones)
Used pixxy widget on kwgt pro for the widgets
Removed gear s plugin( for my smartwatch), Google photos and kwgt pro from being battery optimised
Turned of miui optimisation in developer options
Turned all animations to zero in developer mode
Changed the pointer speed to maximum ( increases touch response to make the phone feel more fast and fluid)
I also use Google camera to get near pixel like photos
Google camera for my phone also supports playground and astrophotography so that's super sweet
AND there you go, I got a phone that looks and feels exactly like stock Android but I also have miui at the base for all it's great battery optimisation and the great features it offers here and there.
snippet.textOriginal:

Changed the pointer speed to maximum ( increases touch response to make the phone feel more fast and fluid)
I also use Google camera to get near pixel like photos 
Google camera for my phone also supports playground and astrophotography so that's super sweet 
AND there you go, I got a phone that looks and feels exactly like stock Android but I also have miui at the base for all it's great battery optimisation and the great features it offers here and there.
